You are building a Next.js 14 App Router project called Vibe Prompt Refiner.

Stack: Next.js 14, TypeScript (strict), Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, Google Gemini API.

Coding rules:
- TypeScript strict mode. No `any` types ever.
- Tailwind only for styling. No inline styles except dynamic values.
- Use shadcn/ui components: Button, Card, Textarea, Select, Badge, Separator.
- Gemini API calls ONLY inside app/api/ route handlers. Never in client components.
- All API response shapes must use types from lib/types.ts.
- Use async/await exclusively. No .then() chains.
- Components live in components/, named PascalCase, single responsibility.
- Add "use client" only when the component uses state or browser APIs.
- Every async action must have a loading state and a user-friendly error state.
- Never expose GEMINI_API_KEY to the client. It's server-side only.
- Validate all user input on both client and server before making API calls.
